Recruiting Offer Scraper
A high-performance Python script that scrapes 247Sports and On3 to identify high school football prospects in a specific graduation class who received their first scholarship offer within the last 7 days.

To maximize speed and respect rate limits, the tool utilizes asynchronous HTTP requests paired with a local CSV caching system.

Features
Dual-Platform Scraping: Extracts recruit data from both 247Sports and On3.

Asynchronous Speed: Powered by asyncio and aiohttp to fetch pages concurrently rather than sequentially.

Smart Caching: Saves previous request data to a local CSV file to minimize redundant network requests and improve subsequent run times.

Anti-Bot Evasion: Integrates undetected-chromedriver for seamless JavaScript rendering and bot-detection bypass.

Progress Tracking: Includes visual progress bars using tqdm to monitor the scraping status in real-time.

Tech Stack & Dependencies
The project relies on the following major Python libraries:

aiohttp & asyncio: For asynchronous network requests.

beautifulsoup4: For parsing HTML and extracting player data.

undetected-chromedriver: For handling dynamic content and bypassing anti-scraping walls.

pandas: For data manipulation, filtering, and managing the CSV cache.

tqdm: For asynchronous and synchronous progress bars.